{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17650470","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17650470"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T21:11:58+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T21:11:58+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18405"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18405","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18405"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11123"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114246"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11123","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11123"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18405"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96246"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"8512"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25784"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25787"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114246","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/114246"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following regulates the sensitivity of muscle spindles?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Alpha motor neuron","Gamma motor neuron","Gamma sensory neuron","Alpha sensory neuron","Interneuron"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGamma motor neurons\u003C/strong\u003E are responsible for regulating the sensitivity of muscle spindles. They innervate the intrafusal fibers within the muscle spindle, adjusting their tension and thus modulating the spindle\u0027s sensitivity to stretch. This allows the muscle spindle to maintain its ability to detect changes in muscle length even when the muscle is contracted.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAlpha motor neurons\u003C/strong\u003E innervate extrafusal muscle fibers, which are responsible for generating force and movement. They do not directly regulate muscle spindle sensitivity.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGamma sensory neurons\u003C/strong\u003E do not exist; sensory information from muscle spindles is carried by type Ia and II afferent fibers.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAlpha sensory neurons\u003C/strong\u003E is not a term used in the context of muscle spindle physiology. Sensory information from muscle spindles is carried by afferent fibers, not motor neurons.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInterneurons\u003C/strong\u003E are involved in reflex arcs and the integration of sensory and motor pathways but do not directly regulate muscle spindle sensitivity.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Gamma motor neurons regulate the sensitivity of muscle spindles by adjusting the tension of intrafusal fibers.","Muscle spindles are sensory receptors within the muscle that detect changes in muscle length and the rate of that change.","Alpha motor neurons innervate extrafusal muscle fibers, which are responsible for muscle contraction."],"references":["Hall JE. Guyton and Hall Textbook of Medical Physiology. 14th ed. Philadelphia: Elsevier; 2021. Chapter 55; pg. 686","Patton KT, Thibodeau GA. Anthony\u0027s Textbook of Anatomy \u0026 Physiology-E-Book: Anthony\u0027s Textbook of Anatomy \u0026 Physiology-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences; 2018.","Hutson M, Ward A, editors. Oxford textbook of musculoskeletal medicine. Oxford University Press; 2015.","Longo UG, Denaro V, editors. T